flowRoot.flowPara: As of 9th August, 4,213 deaths had been registered which mentioned COVID-19
The highest number of COVID-19 deaths were registered in week 17 (20th to 26th April).
Most deaths have occurred among the older population
Between weeks 12 and 32 (16th March to 9th August) there were 2,062 (29%) more deaths in the 85+ age group than average For this age group, 20% of deaths involved COVID-19.
In the same period, there were 1,613 excess deaths in the 75-84 age group (25% above average). 17% of deaths (1,411) in this age group involved COVID-19.
Between the same weeks, there were 595 excess deaths in the 65-74 age group (14% above average). In this age group, 13% of deaths (602) involved COVID-19.

Source: Deaths involving coronavirus (COVID-19) in Scotland, week 32 (3rd to 9th August 2020)
